                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, July 26 (PTI): An army court of inquiry has indicted a colonel for outraging the modesty of an officer of major rank, setting the stage for his court martial. The major has accused Anurodh Mishra of molesting her during their posting in Jammu and Kashmir.          In an attempt to seek relief, Mishra approached the Armed Forces tribunal. But the Tribunal refused to entertain his pleas.                  
	 Mumbai: The death sentence awarded to Ajmal Kasab is likely to come up for confirmation before Bombay High Court next week with the confirmation petition being forwarded by a special court, reports our special correspondent.                  
	 Erode (PTI): A 13-year-old boy has been admitted to hospital in Tamil Nadus Erode allegedly after being beaten by his schools headmaster for accidentally bumping into a girl while travelling on a school bus, police said on Monday. The boys father has lodged a police complaint.                  
	Mysore (PTI): An employee climbed atop the Mysore Urban Development Authority building on Monday morning and threatened to jump. Manjunath, a Group D employee, had said he was dejected because seniors were allegedly harassing him. He came down after officials assured him that his complaint would be addressed.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): A young man was arrested on Monday for allegedly forcing his girlfriend, a Class XII student, to undergo abortion, police have said. Mohammad Tariq of Poonch had forcibly picked up the girl from her house and taken her to a local hospital where the abortion was performed, the police said.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Actor Paresh Rawal and his wife Swaroop Sampat have turned brand ambassadors for National Burn Institutes drive to promote skin donation for burn victims. The couple have pledged to donate their skin and conduct campaigns.
                                                                                                                                              
